explanation.en:
This patient with a heavy smoking history, weight loss, cough, and a mediastinal mass with evidence of metastases (ie, supraclavicular node elargement) has small cell lung cancer (SCLC), also known as oat cell carcinoma. SCLC makes up 10%-20% of all primary lung malignancies and is strongly associated with smoking. It is usually centrally located and arises from the primitive cells of the basal layer of the bronchial epithelium. On light microscopy, small, round or oval cells with scant cytoplasm, hyperchromatic (blue) nuclei, and granular chromatin are visualized. The cells, which may resemble lymphocytes but are typically larger, form clusters or sheets. Abundant mitoses are usually seen. {{exhibit_1}}

Small cell carcinomas can display varying degrees of neuroendocrine differentiation. Immunohistochemical stains are frequently positive for neuroendocrine markers, such as neuron-specific enolase, chromogranin, neural cell adhesion molecule (CD56), and synaptophysin. On electron microscopy, some of the cells have secretory granules in the cytoplasm.

(Choice A) Adenocarcinoma is the most common form of cancer in both nonsmokers and the total population. It is histologically characterized by glandular differentiation (eg, gland formation, mucin production), and the tumor cells often show abundant cytoplasm and eccentrically placed nuclei. The cells often stain positive for mucin. It typically arises in the periphery of the lung.

(Choice B) Hodgkin lymphoma typically presents with cervical lymphadenopathy and can cause a mediastinal mass. However, microscopy demonstrates Reed-Sternberg cells (large cell with multilobed nucleus or multiple nuclei, prominent nucleoli, abundant cytoplasm, and an "owl's eye" appearance) in a background of inflammatory cells. In addition, other B symptoms (eg, fever, night sweats) are common. {{exhibit_2}}

(Choice C) Papillary thyroid carcinoma presents with a thyroid nodule and cervical lymphadenopathy but can also cause an anterior mediastinal mass. Histology reveals branching papillae, which are composed of a fibrovascular stalk covered by neoplastic cuboidal cells with clear ("ground-glass") nuclei. Psammoma bodies (laminated calcium deposits) can sometimes be seen. {{exhibit_3}}

(Choice E) Squamous cell carcinoma typically arises centrally and is composed of polygonal cells with eosinophilic cytoplasm and distinct borders. Well-differentiated squamous cell carcinomas show keratin pearls and intercellular bridges on light microscopy. {{exhibit_4}}

Educational objective:
Small cell lung cancer is strongly associated with smoking and is usually centrally located. Histopathology shows small round/oval cells with scant cytoplasm, hyperchromatic (blue) nuclei, and granular chromatin: abundant mitoses are also usually seen. Immunohistochemical stains are frequently positive for neuroendocrine markers (eg, chromogranin, synaptophysin, neural cell adhesion molecule [CD56]). {{exhibit_5}}

explanation.zh:
这位患者有严重的吸烟史、体重减轻、咳嗽，以及纵隔肿块伴有转移证据（即，锁骨上淋巴结肿大），患有小细胞肺癌（SCLC），也称为燕麦细胞癌。SCLC 占所有原发性肺部恶性肿瘤的 10%-20%，与吸烟密切相关。它通常位于中央，起源于支气管上皮基底层的原始细胞。在光学显微镜下，可见细胞小而圆或卵圆形，细胞质稀少，核呈高度染色（蓝色），染色质呈颗粒状。这些细胞可能类似于淋巴细胞，但通常较大，形成簇或片。通常可见大量有丝分裂。{{exhibit_1}}

小细胞癌可以显示不同程度的神经内分泌分化。免疫组织化学染色经常对神经内分泌标志物呈阳性，例如神经元特异性烯醇化酶、嗜铬粒蛋白、神经细胞粘附分子（CD56）和突触结合蛋白。在电子显微镜下，一些细胞的细胞质中有分泌颗粒。

(选项 A) 腺癌是非吸烟者和总人群中最常见的癌症形式。它在组织学上以腺体分化为特征（例如，腺体形成、粘蛋白产生），并且肿瘤细胞通常显示丰富的细胞质和偏心放置的细胞核。细胞通常对粘蛋白呈阳性染色。它通常起源于肺的周围。

(选项 B) 霍奇金淋巴瘤通常表现为颈部淋巴结病，并可引起纵隔肿块。然而，显微镜下显示 Reed-Sternberg 细胞（大细胞，具有多叶核或多个核，明显的核仁，丰富的细胞质，以及“猫头鹰眼”外观）位于炎性细胞的背景中。此外，其他 B 症状（例如，发烧、盗汗）也很常见。{{exhibit_2}}

(选项 C) 乳头状甲状腺癌表现为甲状腺结节和颈部淋巴结病，但也可引起前纵隔肿块。组织学显示分支乳头，由纤维血管蒂组成，覆盖着具有透明（“毛玻璃状”）核的肿瘤性立方细胞。有时可以看到砂粒体（层状钙沉积）。{{exhibit_3}}

(选项 E) 鳞状细胞癌通常起源于中央，由具有嗜酸性细胞质和清晰边界的多边形细胞组成。分化良好的鳞状细胞癌在光学显微镜下显示角蛋白珠和细胞间桥。{{exhibit_4}}

教育目标：
小细胞肺癌与吸烟密切相关，通常位于中央。组织病理学显示细胞小而圆/卵圆形，细胞质稀少，核呈高度染色（蓝色），染色质呈颗粒状：通常也可见大量有丝分裂。免疫组织化学染色经常对神经内分泌标志物呈阳性（例如，嗜铬粒蛋白、突触结合蛋白、神经细胞粘附分子 [CD56]）。{{exhibit_5}}
